<item>
            <title>[LU-313] lfsck.sh test is not actually running lfsck</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-313</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The current lustre/tests/lfsck.sh test script is being run by Jenkins/auster/whatever, but in actuality the script is not running the &quot;lfsck&quot; part of the test because SKIP_LFSCK=yes is always set in test-framework.sh due to the old bug 13698.  However, this bug should be fixed &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, the lfsck.sh script itself should be changed so that it checks for &quot;SKIP_LFSCK == yes&quot; rather than &quot;SKIP_LFSCK != no&quot; so that without any external specification otherwise it will properly run the distributed lfsck part of the test.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="10808">LU-313</key>
            <summary>lfsck.sh test is not actually running lfsck</summary>
